characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age at baseline, calculated as the integer part of (date of informed consent – date of birth + 1)/365.25.

characteristics.name: Body Mass Index
characteristics.description: Body mass index (BMI) at baseline, calculated as weight (kg) / [height (m)]^2.

characteristics.name: Treatment cohort
characteristics.description: Participant cohort classification: Cohort 1 (treatment experienced, >28 days of WD therapy) or Cohort 2 (treatment naïve, ≤28 days of WD therapy).

characteristics.name: Medical history
characteristics.description: Participant's medical history, summarized by system organ class (SOC) and preferred term (PT).

characteristics.name: Prior medications for Wilson Disease
characteristics.description: Prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease.

characteristics.name: Baseline copper balance
characteristics.description: Copper balance measured during the pretreatment period (Day -4 through Day -1).

characteristics.name: Baseline molybdenum balance
characteristics.description: Molybdenum balance measured during the pretreatment period (Day -4 through Day -1).

characteristics.name: Baseline laboratory assessments
characteristics.description: Clinical laboratory test results at baseline.
